  "body": "<!-- Please use this template while reporting a bug and provide as much info as possible. Not doing so may result in your bug not being addressed in a timely manner. Thanks!-->\r\n\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nThe signal SIGTERM has no effect for `hyperkube kube-proxy`, `hyperkube kube-controller-manager`, `hyperkube kube-scheduler`.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nSame behavior for all the components, sending SIGTERM once shuts down the components correctly.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\nStart `hyperkube kube-proxy`, press Ctrl-C, doesn't work, press Ctrl-C again kills the process. Start `hyperkube kubelet`, press Ctrl-C stops the process immediately.\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\nFor `hyperkube kubelet`, `hyperkube kube-apiserver` it seems to work fine. Sending the signal twice works as well, probably with panic.\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): 1.11.4, 1.12.3\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration: Baremetal\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release): Redhat 7\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`): 3.10.0-862.14.4.el7.x86_64\r\n- Install tools: Manual, Systemd\r\n- Others:\r\n\r\n<!-- DO NOT EDIT BELOW THIS LINE -->\r\n/kind bug",
